00:18:23,799 --> 00:18:25,626
我连清洁工都不会给他做
SAM: I wouldn't give the bum a mop job.

323
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:28,298
别无选择，我必须照顾他们
I had no choice. I had to take care of them.

324
00:18:28,513 --> 00:18:30,173
这些乡巴佬当权
These yokels ran the state.

325
00:18:30,307 --> 00:18:31,421
多谢，议员
DEALER: Thanks, Senator.

326
00:18:31,558 --> 00:18:35,093
-他们立法，又掌管法院
-我要开房间
SAM: They passed the laws,
owned the courts.
I need a room.

327
00:18:35,730 --> 00:18:39,680
我每周都有十多个政客来访
SAM: I had dozens of politicians
and state officials coming through weekly.

328
00:18:39,818 --> 00:18:41,692
-他要什么都给他
-当然
SAM: Get him what he wants.
BILLY: Certainly.

329
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:43,195
何不让他们快乐？
SAM: Why not make them happy?

330
00:18:45,258 --> 00:18:49,456
[Upbeat R&B music]

331
00:18:55,378 --> 00:18:58,249
对于政客
例如我们这位州议员…
For politicians,
like our State Senator up there...

332
00:18:58,506 --> 00:18:59,964
一切都是免费的
everything was on the house.

333
00:19:00,050 --> 00:19:03,051
他们的招待生涯
在当选时就赢得了
These guys won their comped life
when they got elected.

334
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,888
<font color=#38B0DE>-=字幕:CHD720P代刻=-</font>

335
00:19:03,178 --> 00:19:04,720
何不加以利用？
Why not take advantage of it?

336
00:19:05,848 --> 00:19:09,513
政客还是小事，我们解决的了
Still, the politicians came cheap.
We could handle them.

337
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:11,919
是像市川那种…
It's a whale, like K.K. Ichikawa...

338
00:19:12,119 --> 00:19:14,931
百家乐一把下三万的豪赌客
who plays $30, 000 a hand in baccarat.

339
00:19:15,025 --> 00:19:16,934
这种才该看紧
That's the one you really gotta watch.

340
00:19:17,069 --> 00:19:20,520
他下注动作快，玩得大
他的资金雄厚…
He plays fast and big.
He has the cash and the credit...

341
00:19:20,657 --> 00:19:22,032
足可把你玩垮
to turn out your lights.

342
00:19:22,159 --> 00:19:25,694
一年前他让开曼群岛上
好几家赌场洗底
A year ago he cleaned out a couple
of casinos in the Cayman Islands.

343
00:19:26,247 --> 00:19:28,453
他从赌场赢了我们两百万…
Downstairs he takes us for $2 million...

344
00:19:28,624 --> 00:19:32,373
又从酒店套房拿了免费的
肥皂、洗发精与毛巾
and upstairs he takes free soap,
shampoo and towels.

345
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:35,999
又是一个
喜爱免费套房…
Another billionaire cheapskate
who loved his free rooms...

346
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:39,253
免费私人飞机又赚得我们两百万
的亿万富翁小气鬼
free private jets
and $2 million of our money.

347
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:42,092
我们也不好惹
But we got him back.

348
00:19:42,224 --> 00:19:44,762
我让机师告诉他飞机故障
I had our pilot tell him
the plane was on the fritz.

349
00:19:44,893 --> 00:19:47,218
-发生什么事？
-非常抱歉
ICHIKAWA: What went wrong?
BILLY: I'm awfully sorry.

350
00:19:48,064 --> 00:19:49,938
是机械故障
These mechanical things happen.

351
00:19:50,066 --> 00:19:52,355
在这儿总比在上面好
Better here than up there.

352
00:19:52,736 --> 00:19:55,274
然后他赶不上回日本的飞机
SAM: Then he missed the flights
connecting with Japan.

353
00:19:55,405 --> 00:19:57,777
竟然没有空房
I can't believe there's no room.

354
00:20:02,664 --> 00:20:06,033
我们给了他一整楼的房间
SAM: We got him back with
a whole floor of rooms to himself.

355
00:20:06,168 --> 00:20:09,122
-真抱歉让你赶不上飞机
-你想要赢回我的钱啊
-Sorry you missed your plane.
-You'd like some of my money back.

356
00:20:09,255 --> 00:20:10,811
不，不赌了
Oh, no. No gambling.

357
00:20:11,011 --> 00:20:13,172
[Upbeat R&B music]

358
00:20:13,969 --> 00:20:16,638
他回来后开始下小注
SAM: And once he was back,
he played small.

359
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,969
一把只赌一千
而不是平常的三万一把
He bet $1,000 a hand,
instead of his usual $30,000 a hand.

360
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:29,521
但我知道这些豪赌客的习性…
But I knew the trick
with whales like Ichikawa...

361
00:20:29,653 --> 00:20:32,108
他们不可能一直下小注的
was that they can't bet small for long.

362
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:34,570
他不觉得是赢一万…
He didn't think of it as winning $10, 000...

363
00:20:34,659 --> 00:20:37,114
他会想成是输九万…
he thought of it as losing $90, 000.

364
00:20:37,955 --> 00:20:39,829
所以他开始加码
So, he upped his bets.

365
00:20:43,962 --> 00:20:48,007
直到他将赢得的输光
再加上自己一百万的现金
Until he dropped his winnings back
and gave up $1 million of his own cash.

366
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:53,841
在赌场里，第一原则就是
让他们一直赌…
In a casino, the cardinal rule
is to keep them playing...

367
00:20:53,973 --> 00:20:55,348
也让他们一直回来
and keep them coming back.

368
00:20:55,475 --> 00:20:58,013
赌得越多就输得越多
The longer they play, the more they lose.

369
00:20:58,145 --> 00:20:59,926
最终钱就都是我们的
In the end, we get it all.

370
00:21:00,126 --> 00:21:05,029
[Upbeat R&B music]

371
00:21:09,658 --> 00:21:12,861
在赌城，每个人都得注意着别人
In Vegas, everybody's gotta watch
everybody else.

372
00:21:15,957 --> 00:21:18,578
玩家是来赢赌场钱的…
Since the players
are looking to beat the casino...

373
00:21:20,003 --> 00:21:22,375
庄家得看好玩家…
the dealers are watching the players...

374
00:21:24,342 --> 00:21:26,584
收付赌注得看好庄家…
the boxmen are watching the dealers...

375
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:29,592
管场的注意着收付赌注的人…
the floormen are watching the boxmen...

376
00:21:30,182 --> 00:21:32,755
赌区经理看着管场的…
the pit bosses are watching the floormen...

377
00:21:33,019 --> 00:21:35,854
值班经理看着赌区经理…
the shift bosses are watching
the pit bosses...

378
00:21:35,939 --> 00:21:38,726
赌场经理看着值班经理…
the casino manager is watching
the shift bosses...

379
00:21:38,859 --> 00:21:41,017
我则看着赌场经理…
I'm watching the casino manager...

380
00:21:41,195 --> 00:21:44,398
而监视照相机看着我们大家
and the eye in the sky is watching us all.

381
00:21:48,787 --> 00:21:50,826
另外，还有十多个家伙…
Plus, we had a dozen guys...

382
00:21:50,956 --> 00:21:54,123
大多以前都是老千
他们知道所有的骗术
most of them ex-cheats,
who knew every trick in the house.

383
00:21:54,147 --> 00:21:58,106
[Upbeat R&B music continues]

384
00:22:15,109 --> 00:22:16,188
好啊！
Yes!

385
00:22:16,861 --> 00:22:19,613
-非常好
-我就跟你说我今天很旺
-Very nice.
-I told you I was hot tonight.

386
00:22:31,253 --> 00:22:32,711
好样的
Looking good.

387
00:22:33,297 --> 00:22:35,171
来吧，为了金吉儿，快
MAN: Let's go. This is for Ginger.

388
00:22:35,299 --> 00:22:37,291
一百赌你没老A
MAN: Let me have $100 on your hard 10.

389
00:22:38,344 --> 00:22:39,423
谢谢
Thank you.

390
00:22:40,472 --> 00:22:41,670
来吧
MAN: Here we go now.

391
00:22:42,128 --> 00:22:44,119
[Upbeat R&B music]

392
00:22:52,944 --> 00:22:54,983
-对不起
-骰子
-Oh, I'm sorry.
-The dice.

393
00:22:56,991 --> 00:22:58,782
多谢
Thank you very much.

394
00:23:00,662 --> 00:23:02,120
多谢你
I appreciate that.

395
00:23:02,831 --> 00:23:05,369
保重，史蒂夫
要冒险啊，开快车
Take care, Steve. Take chances, drive fast.

396
00:23:06,544 --> 00:23:08,999
这一百给你，甜心
多谢你赏光
This $100 is for you, love.
Thanks for your time.

397
00:23:10,632 --> 00:23:12,459
-快点
-怎么了？
-Come on.
-What's the matter?

398
00:23:13,468 --> 00:23:16,173
我帮你赚了不少，我要我的份
I made a lot of money for you, I want my cut.

399
00:23:16,305 --> 00:23:18,096
什么钱？我看到你偷钱
What money? I've seen you stealing.

400
00:23:18,224 --> 00:23:19,833
“什么钱？”
你看看这堆筹码
"What money?" Look at the stack of chips.

401
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:22,135
-我要我的一半
-我观察你一夜了
GINGER: I want my half.
GAMBLER: I've watched you.

402
00:23:22,235 --> 00:23:24,538
-我要我的钱
-你皮包里全是熟筹码
-I want my money.
-Your bag is full of chips.

403
00:23:24,738 --> 00:23:28,037
-我才没偷你的东西
-滚吧！
GINGER: I didn't steal anything from you.
GAMBLER: Get lost!

404
00:23:28,108 --> 00:23:29,776
-滚吧？
-没错！
GINGER: Get lost?
GAMBLER: Yes!

405
00:23:29,976 --> 00:23:32,345
-这怎么样呢？
-别这样！
-Well, how about that?
-Come on!

406
00:23:32,545 --> 00:23:34,740
[Upbeat R&B music continues]

407
00:23:52,299 --> 00:23:56,133
[Romantic pop music]

408
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:27,320
真酷，让我一见钟情
SAM: What a move. I fell in love right there.

409
00:24:27,454 --> 00:24:30,704
但在赌城，像金吉儿这样的女孩
得花上大钱
But in Vegas, for a girl like Ginger,
love costs money.

410
00:24:30,904 --> 00:24:35,568
[Romantic rock music]

411
00:24:36,798 --> 00:24:38,506
我去补个妆
I'm gonna go powder my nose.

412
00:24:49,730 --> 00:24:52,897
-金吉儿的人生目标是钱
-马上回来
SAM: Ginger's mission in life was money.
I'll be right back.

413
00:24:53,025 --> 00:24:55,064
-待会见，金吉儿
-多谢你
DOORMAN: See you.
GINGER: Thanks for asking.

414
00:24:55,153 --> 00:24:56,861
她在赌场可是皇后
SAM: She was a queen around the casino.

415
00:24:56,988 --> 00:25:00,404
她召来大赌客
并也帮他们花大钱
She brought in high rollers
and helped them spend a lot of money.

416
00:25:00,784 --> 00:25:02,990
-你好
-嘿，金吉儿，你好吗？
-Hello.
-Hey, Ginger. How you doing?

417
00:25:03,079 --> 00:25:05,784
好得很，一点小意思
你帮我搞定了吗？
GINGER: Great. You might have
something for me. Got me covered?

418
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:09,122
-非常感谢
-自己保重喔
GINGER: Thank you.
VALET: Take care of yourself.

419
00:25:09,211 --> 00:25:11,287
我有些幸运丸给你，安迪
I got some lucky pills for you, Andy.

420
00:25:11,922 --> 00:25:13,980
谁不想要金吉儿？
她是城里名声最响亮…
SAM: Who didn't want her?
She was one of the best known...

421
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:17,843
也是道上最受欢迎的江湖人物
best liked and most respected hustlers
in town.

422
00:25:21,767 --> 00:25:24,139
像她这么聪明的玩家
可以让男人…
Smart hustlers like her
could keep a guy awake...

423
00:25:24,228 --> 00:25:26,683
两三天不睡
然后再让他一文不名的…
for two or three days
before sending him home broke...

424
00:25:26,773 --> 00:25:28,628
回到老婆与银行审查主任身边
to the little woman and his bank examiners.

425
00:25:28,828 --> 00:25:32,889
[Romantic rock music continues]

426
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:45,585
有找钱吗？
Any change?

427
00:25:46,754 --> 00:25:50,253
我回来时小赌了几把
Oh, I hit a few games on the way back.

428
00:25:51,593 --> 00:25:54,677
那根本是胡扯
她把钱收起来了
SAM: But that was all bullshit.
She just pocketed the cash.

429
00:25:57,458 --> 00:25:59,332
-你今天好吗？
-不错啊
GINGER: How you doing tonight?
CASHIER: Good.

430
00:25:59,461 --> 00:26:01,003
-你呢？
-衰死了
CASHIER: How are you?
GINGER: Beat.

431
00:26:01,129 --> 00:26:04,391
-金吉儿洞悉玩家们的习性
-给你一百
SAM: Ginger had the hustlers' code.
GINGER: Take one for you.

432
00:26:04,842 --> 00:26:07,713
-多谢
-她懂得如何买通他人
CASHIER: Thank you.
SAM: She knew how to take care of people.

433
00:26:07,845 --> 00:26:09,921
这就是赌城的座右铭
That's what Vegas is all about.

434
00:26:10,056 --> 00:26:12,511
-六千八百元
-谢啦
CASHIER: $6,800.
GINGER: Thanks.

435
00:26:12,643 --> 00:26:15,181
-这里是讲究回扣的城市
-晚安
SAM: It's kickback city.
GINGER: Have a good night.

436
00:26:21,069 --> 00:26:22,978
她罩庄家…
SAM: She took care of the dealers...

437
00:26:23,155 --> 00:26:25,397
赌区经理，管场经理…
pit bosses, floor managers...

438
00:26:25,783 --> 00:26:28,238
但尤其关照停车小弟…
but, mostly, the valet parkers...

439
00:26:28,327 --> 00:26:31,613
他们能帮你找到任何东西
也能帮你解决任何事
the guys who could get you anything
and take care of anything.

440
00:26:31,748 --> 00:26:33,456
金吉儿搞定了停车的…
Ginger took care of the parkers...

441
00:26:33,584 --> 00:26:37,035
他们搞定警卫
而警卫会摆平警察…
who took care of the security guards,
who took care of the cops...

442
00:26:37,171 --> 00:26:39,559
-让她可继续开工
-我今晚需要那东西
who let her operate.
I need that stuff tonight.

443
00:26:39,883 --> 00:26:42,125
-没问题
-你真好
VALET: No problem.
GINGER: You are a doll.

444
00:26:42,511 --> 00:26:44,753
停车赚的钱多到…
SAM: The valet parking job
was such a money-maker...

445
00:26:44,847 --> 00:26:48,050
得买通酒店经理才能排上空缺
they had to pay off the hotel manager
just to get the concession.

446
00:26:50,061 --> 00:26:52,267
不过有一点我不懂…
But one thing I didn't understand...

447
00:26:52,397 --> 00:26:54,852
她将一切都控制的好好的…
was that she had everything under control...

448
00:26:55,025 --> 00:26:57,730
却被她那拉皮条的男友
莱丝特戴蒙德吃得死死的
except for her old pimp boyfriend,
Lester Diamond.

449
00:26:57,862 --> 00:27:00,104
我得顾到其他人，我的搭挡们
I got other people in this. I got partners.

450
00:27:01,407 --> 00:27:05,108
在这事上有我罩你，知道吗？
I'm looking out for you in this thing, okay?

451
00:27:05,370 --> 00:27:09,071
你将获你应得的
而且第一个拿到，好吗？
You'll get yours back,
and you'll get it back first. Okay?

452
00:27:09,208 --> 00:27:11,414
-好的
-你去哪儿了？
-All right.
-Where you going?

453
00:27:12,712 --> 00:27:14,455
你在哪儿？
你又飘走了
Where are you? You're in that place.

454
00:27:14,548 --> 00:27:16,457
-我在这儿
-不，你不在
-I'm here.
-No, you're not.

455
00:27:16,592 --> 00:27:17,623
你在哪？
Where are you?

456
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:21,262
我永远在你身边
I'm always here for you.

457
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:24,846
-真的
-是啊
-You are.
-I am.

458
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:28,432
我所认识的金吉儿
根本不会多看这怪胎一眼
SAM: The Ginger I knew
wouldn't even look at this creep.

459
00:27:29,899 --> 00:27:31,559
-祝你好运
-是啊
-Good luck.
-Yeah.

460
00:27:31,901 --> 00:27:33,609
他是个老千，专作假牌…
SAM: He was a moocher, a card cheat...

461
00:27:33,737 --> 00:27:36,406
老在高尔夫俱乐部招摇撞骗
一个瘪三…
a country club golf hustler, a scumbag...

462
00:27:36,865 --> 00:27:39,403
-为了几块钱追着牙医屁股跑
-小心点
-chasing dentists for a few bucks.
-Careful.

463
00:27:39,577 --> 00:27:41,902
他永远都没钱，永远都有藉口
SAM: He was always broke.
He always had a story.

464
00:27:42,038 --> 00:27:44,077
不知为何，她却拒绝不了他
Somehow, she could never turn him down.

465
00:27:44,416 --> 00:27:47,702
在金吉儿眼里，他只是运气不好
The way Ginger saw it
was that he was just an unlucky guy.

466
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:49,747
总得有人照顾他
Somebody had to take care of him.

467
00:27:50,381 --> 00:27:51,412
在老家
BACK HOME

468
00:27:51,507 --> 00:27:53,298
但尼奇可不需要人照顾
But nobody had to take care of Nicky.

469
00:27:53,426 --> 00:27:56,095
你找到现金的话
我们就跟你平分
You find any cash in there,
we'll whack it up with you.

470
00:27:56,179 --> 00:27:58,385
他把自己照顾得太好了
SAM: He took care of himself only too well.

471
00:27:58,724 --> 00:28:01,262
这也是为什么老家的条子
都想抓他到案
That's why every badge back home
wanted to nail him.

472
00:28:01,394 --> 00:28:05,012
我将这些都折得好好的
能不能放尊重点
I folded these things beautifully.
I would appreciate a little respect.

473
00:28:05,273 --> 00:28:07,479
别看我，兄弟
我还得跟她同床共枕
Don't look at me, pal, I gotta live with her.

474
00:28:08,610 --> 00:28:11,315
就连去渡个假
他们在机场时都不放过他
SAM: Even after a vacation,
they hassled him at the airport.

475
00:28:11,447 --> 00:28:14,152
法兰克玛雷诺在那儿等他
条子们也在
Frank Marino was there to meet him.
So were the cops.

476
00:28:14,284 --> 00:28:15,992
他们想逮他…
They wanted to pinch him...

477
00:28:16,077 --> 00:28:18,615
-因为一宗在安特卫普的钻石窃案
-帮忙折吧
-for a diamond burglary in Antwerp.
-Help me fold these.

478
00:28:18,705 --> 00:28:21,741
他们随时愿意嫁祸于他
不管是在哪儿发生什么事
SAM: They were ready to blame him
