驳回罗斯坦的申请书在此动议
...this Commission acts on a motion
denying the Rothstein application.

1838
01:44:33,773 --> 01:44:37,048
-驳回？
-有人赞成驳回吗？
COUNSELOR: Denying?
SENATOR: Do I hear a motion seconded?

1839
01:44:37,110 --> 01:44:38,678
主席先生，我赞成
Mr. Chairman, I second the motion.

1840
01:44:38,878 --> 01:44:40,513
还有赞同票吗？
Do I have a vote on the motion?

1841
01:44:40,713 --> 01:44:41,714
同意！
-Aye!
-Aye!

1842
01:44:41,914 --> 01:44:42,938
Aye!

1843
01:44:43,149 --> 01:44:45,649
同意票获胜，听证会结束
The ayes have it. This hearing is adjourned.

1844
01:44:45,777 --> 01:44:48,943
-开什么玩笑
-什么叫结束？
-You have to be kidding.
-Adjourned? What do you mean?

1845
01:44:49,188 --> 01:44:53,660
议员，你答应我一场听证会的
你连联邦调查局的报告都没看
Senator, you promised me a hearing.
You didn't even look at the FBI reports.

1846
01:44:53,860 --> 01:44:58,832
你来坦吉乐作客时
不是答应我会有公平的听证会？
When you were my guest at the Tangiers
Hotel, didn't you promise me a fair hearing?

1847
01:44:59,032 --> 01:45:02,502
-我从未是你的客人
-不是我的客人？我没招待过你？
SENATOR: I was never your guest.
SAM: Never my guest? I never comped you?

1848
01:45:02,702 --> 01:45:04,904
难道我一个月
没有最少招待你三次？
I don't comp you
at least three times a month?

1849
01:45:05,104 --> 01:45:07,373
我现在回答这个问题
I'd like to answer that at this time.

1850
01:45:07,573 --> 01:45:10,877
罗斯坦先生的反应很常见
他在撒谎
Mr. Rothstein is being very typical
to this point. He's lying.

1851
01:45:11,077 --> 01:45:14,981
我唯一一次去过坦吉乐
就是巴尼葛林斯坦那次晚宴
The only time I was at the Tangiers
was a dinner with Barney Greenstein.

1852
01:45:15,181 --> 01:45:17,750
-我当时在场吗？
-你四处周旋着
Was I at the dinner?
SENATOR: You were wandering around.

1853
01:45:17,950 --> 01:45:20,920
-我在场吗？
-你四处周旋
SAM: Was I at that dinner?
SENATOR: You were wandering.

1854
01:45:21,120 --> 01:45:24,057
-你在室内
-我在室内？
SENATOR: You were in the building.
SAM: I was in the building?

1855
01:45:24,257 --> 01:45:28,595
你很清楚我在那儿
你向我保证会有公正的听证会
You know damn well I was there.
You swore I would have a fair hearing.

1856
01:45:28,795 --> 01:45:31,651
没有吗？
Did you not?

1857
01:45:32,732 --> 01:45:36,620
至少承认说我那天在场
这总可以了吧
Tell me I was at least at the dinner.
Allow me that much.

1858
01:45:36,702 --> 01:45:39,172
-至少也得说我在场吧！
-是，你在
SAM: Give me that much at least!
SENATOR: Yes, you were.

1859
01:45:39,372 --> 01:45:42,864
多谢你没说我是骗子
你这个狗东西
Thanks for not calling me a liar,
you son of a bitch.

1860
01:45:44,277 --> 01:45:47,547
一场例行的听证会
在昨晚成了一场闹剧…
A routine licensing hearing
turned into bedlam yesterday...

1861
01:45:47,747 --> 01:45:51,084
当抢眼的坦吉乐高层
山姆“艾斯”罗斯坦…
when the flamboyant Tangiers Casino
executive, Sam "Ace" Rothstein...

1862
01:45:51,284 --> 01:45:54,187
指控赌博游乐委员会高官贪污
accused top gaming officials of corruption.

1863
01:45:54,387 --> 01:45:57,123
你在我的旅馆接受招待
并答应我会有公平的听证会
...promised me a fair hearing
when you were comped at my hotel?

1864
01:45:57,323 --> 01:46:00,760
你还要求将你的帐单挂公帐
And you asked for copies of your bill
to put on your expense account.

1865
01:46:00,960 --> 01:46:03,897
当赌博游乐执照被驳回时大吼大叫…
In a wild outburst that followed his gaming
license denial...

1866
01:46:04,097 --> 01:46:04,663
Bullshit!

1867
01:46:04,863 --> 01:46:06,299
-狗屁！
-罗斯坦与好几名…
...Rothstein followed several...

1868
01:46:06,499 --> 01:46:10,650
错愕的委员到走道
并持续着他的指控…
stunned commissioners into the hallway
where he continued his harangue...

1869
01:46:10,744 --> 01:46:13,235
直到他的律师与朋友劝他离开
until his own lawyers and friends
urged him to leave.

1870
01:46:13,372 --> 01:46:16,876
你有过去，我也有过去
我的不见得比你的糟糕
You have a past. I have a past.
My past is no worse than yours.

1871
01:46:17,076 --> 01:46:19,545
你们还自以为有权去判决别人！
You guys think you have
the right to pass judgment!

1872
01:46:19,745 --> 01:46:22,815
被怀疑长期无照管理坦吉乐…
NEWSREADER: Long suspected
of running Tangiers without a license...

1873
01:46:23,015 --> 01:46:27,420
昨天的听证会本是要决议
像罗斯坦如此背景的人…
yesterday's hearing was to determine
if someone with Rothstein's history...

1874
01:46:27,620 --> 01:46:30,556
是否有资格正式在赌博游乐界
担任如此高的职位
was qualified to officially hold
a top gaming post.

1875
01:46:30,756 --> 01:46:33,424
罗斯坦玩完了
王八伪君子！
REMO: Fucking hypocrites!

1876
01:46:33,493 --> 01:46:36,829
-他现在怎么办？
-我不知道
-What the hell's he gonna do now?
-I don't know.

1877
01:46:37,029 --> 01:46:38,398
他在干嘛？
What's he doing?

1878
01:46:38,598 --> 01:46:41,401
他也知道他大吼大叫的那群人
都是我们的朋友
He knows all those guys he yelled at
are friends of ours.

1879
01:46:41,601 --> 01:46:43,836
他是怎么了，搞得一团糟？
What's the matter with him,
making all this mess?

1880
01:46:44,036 --> 01:46:46,239
他或许可以用另一个头衔管事
Maybe he could run things
with another job title.

1881
01:46:46,439 --> 01:46:48,841
这不是最好的
但我们又能如何呢？
Won't be the best,
but what are we gonna do?

1882
01:46:49,041 --> 01:46:53,246
他不论管什么，都得安静点
让他躲到楼上办公室去
REMO: However he runs things, it's gotta be
quiet. Let him hide upstairs in the office.

1883
01:46:53,446 --> 01:46:56,247
说他是工友，我不在乎
Say he's a janitor. I don't give a shit.

1884
01:46:56,460 --> 01:47:01,371
但拜托，不管他做什么
都得低调点
But please, whatever job he takes,
make sure it's something quiet.

1885
01:47:09,295 --> 01:47:11,097
各位先生与女士…
ANNOUNCER: [On TV]
Ladies and gentlemen...

1886
01:47:11,297 --> 01:47:13,866
坦吉乐大饭店
非常荣幸能为您介绍…
the Tangiers Hotel
proudly presents the all-new...

1887
01:47:14,066 --> 01:47:17,564
山姆罗斯坦秀，艾斯的单人牌
Sam Rothstein show, Aces High.

1888
01:47:17,650 --> 01:47:18,645
艾斯的单人牌

1889
01:47:20,706 --> 01:47:23,443
今晚，从最新的球赛赌区
现场实况转播…
Tonight, taped live
from the all-new sports book...

1890
01:47:23,643 --> 01:47:26,779
我们为您带来艾斯的单人牌的
首次演出…
we present the premiere showing
of Aces High...

1891
01:47:26,979 --> 01:47:29,990
连同莎夏西门诺夫交响乐团…
with the Sasha Semenoff Orchestra...

1892
01:47:30,550 --> 01:47:33,786
与山姆罗斯坦舞群！
and the Sam Rothstein dancers!

1893
01:47:35,021 --> 01:47:39,726
罗斯坦先生是位职业赌徒
也是全美最棒的美式足球下注者
Mr. Rothstein is a professional gambler
and the best U.S. football handicapper.

1894
01:47:39,926 --> 01:47:45,259
一位能带领你进入
真正的拉斯维加斯的人
A man who will take you inside the real
Las Vegas as no one has ever done before.

1895
01:47:45,264 --> 01:47:49,469
现在让我们欢迎
坦吉乐赌场新的娱乐董事…
Now, the new entertainment director
of the Tangiers Hotel Casino...

1896
01:47:49,669 --> 01:47:51,304
山姆罗斯坦先生
Mr. Sam Rothstein.

1897
01:47:51,504 --> 01:47:53,836
[Audience applauding]

1898
01:47:53,973 --> 01:47:58,933
[Band playing upbeat dance music]

1899
01:48:00,846 --> 01:48:05,018
欢迎来到山姆罗斯坦秀
很高兴你们能参与
Welcome to the Sam Rothstein show.
We're happy to have you here this evening.

1900
01:48:05,218 --> 01:48:08,087
我左边的这位小姐是特茹蒂…
The young lady to my left is Trudy...

1901
01:48:08,287 --> 01:48:11,357
她是我们巴黎秀新的首席舞者
who is a lead new dancer
in our fabulous show from Paris.

1902
01:48:11,557 --> 01:48:14,622
我们今晚的第一位来宾…
Our first guest this evening...

1903
01:48:15,361 --> 01:48:17,374
法兰克艾华伦
is Frankie Avalon.

1904
01:48:22,535 --> 01:48:25,905
-看好他
-我有个大家庭
PAT: Keep an eye on him.
FRANKIE: I've got a large family.

1905
01:48:26,105 --> 01:48:31,143
-你有几个孩子？
-我很自豪的说，八个
SAM: How many kids do you have?
I'm very proud to say, eight children.

1906
01:48:33,813 --> 01:48:37,617
-太了不起了
-没什么，是我的荣幸
-That's amazing.
-There's nothing to it. It was my pleasure.

1907
01:48:37,817 --> 01:48:39,079
[Audience laughing]

1908
01:48:39,151 --> 01:48:40,978
别这样
PHILIP: Ace, don't do it.

1909
01:48:45,324 --> 01:48:47,157
天啊
Jesus.

1910
01:48:47,260 --> 01:48:48,895
他在耍杂技！
He's juggling!

1911
01:48:49,095 --> 01:48:52,698
我们别对县辅导
派特委布太认真
SAM: Let's not take County Commissioner
Pat Webb too seriously.

1912
01:48:52,898 --> 01:48:56,402
我最近本想邀他在节目上辩论的
但是他拒绝了
I recently challenged him to a debate
on this program, and he declined.

1913
01:48:56,602 --> 01:49:01,635
你在担心什么呢，派特？
你不需要事先给我问题
What are you worried about, Pat?
You don't have to send me any questions.

1914
01:49:01,907 --> 01:49:03,943
你什么都可以问我
You can ask me anything you want.

1915
01:49:04,143 --> 01:49:07,010
他在电视上干嘛？
ANDY: What the hell is he doing
on television?

1916
01:49:07,146 --> 01:49:12,394
他整晚都在上面
喊着要将他的案子告上最高法院
He's on all night, screaming about
taking his lawsuit to the Supreme Court.

1917
01:49:12,451 --> 01:49:16,186
他真是疯了
他想将这带到华府去？
He really must be crazy.
He's gonna go to Washington with this?

1918
01:49:16,355 --> 01:49:18,606
他简直是疯了
He's out of his fucking mind.

1919
01:49:18,697 --> 01:49:21,828
世上有这样的伪君子真是可叹
他们爱做什么就做什么
It's a pity we have such hypocrisy.
Some people do what they want.

1920
01:49:22,028 --> 01:49:24,797
其他人却得承担后果
这就是人生
Other people have to pay
through the nose. Such is life.

1921
01:49:24,997 --> 01:49:30,657
安迪，去找他
告诉他辞职的时候到了
Andy, go see him. Tell him
maybe it's time he should quit.

1922
01:49:36,008 --> 01:49:38,611
第一点，他们的所做所为
完全的违反了宪法
SAM: First, what they did
was totally unconstitutional.

1923
01:49:38,811 --> 01:49:42,415
我们已在高等法院的等候单上了
SAM: We're on the list to be heard before
the U.S. Supreme Court.

1924
01:49:42,615 --> 01:49:44,784
这些家伙才不在乎高等法院
These guys don't care
about the Supreme Court.

1925
01:49:44,984 --> 01:49:47,887
他们要一切平息，要你别再搞了
They want things to quiet down.
They want you to walk away.

1926
01:49:48,087 --> 01:49:53,025
别搞了？安迪，你不是说真的
你难道看不到这严重性吗？
Walk away? Andy, you can't be serious.
Don't you see what's at stake?

1927
01:49:53,225 --> 01:49:56,028
老头说你的朋友或许该罢手了
The old man said maybe
your friend should give in.

1928
01:49:56,228 --> 01:49:58,931
当老头说“或许”时
就像是教皇发谕令一样
When the old man says "maybe,"
that's like a papal bull.

1929
01:49:59,131 --> 01:50:01,868
你不但该罢手，还该跑路
Not only should you quit, you should run.

1930
01:50:02,068 --> 01:50:07,074
他们每次在报上提到我的名字
就一定扯到尼奇
Every time they mention my name
in the papers, they mention Nicky, too.

1931
01:50:07,166 --> 01:50:08,957
这他妈的有什么帮助？
How the fuck does that help?

1932
01:50:09,008 --> 01:50:11,377
他带来的注目简直是谋杀
The heat he brought down is murder.

1933
01:50:11,577 --> 01:50:14,039
警察局本来很合作
The police department was cooperative.

1934
01:50:14,174 --> 01:50:16,182
他将他们激怒到
现在大家都动不了
They're pissed off.
Nobody can make a move anymore.

1935
01:50:16,382 --> 01:50:17,550
你能怎样呢？
What do you do about that?

1936
01:50:17,750 --> 01:50:20,686
-你想说什么？
-我不知道，他根本不听我的
-What are you proposing?
-I don't know. He doesn't listen to me.

1937
01:50:20,886 --> 01:50:23,656
或许他才该消失一阵子
这样会很糟吗？
Maybe he should get lost for a while.
Would that be so bad?

1938
01:50:23,856 --> 01:50:26,973
-他们不会调走尼奇的
-若他离开一阵…
-They ain't sending Nicky nowhere.
-If he took a break...

1939
01:50:27,104 --> 01:50:28,528
给大家移动布局的机会
it would give everybody time to maneuver.

1940
01:50:28,728 --> 01:50:33,307
别再搞布局的事
赶紧离开吧
I would forget about the maneuver.
I would just get out.

1941
01:50:34,767 --> 01:50:35,825
[Sighs]

1942
01:50:36,769 --> 01:50:38,480
我不能
I can't do that.

1943
01:50:39,105 --> 01:50:43,342
当然，安迪一到家后
尼奇就听说我们的谈话
SAM: Of course, as soon as Andy got home,
Nicky heard about our talk in the car.

1944
01:50:43,542 --> 01:50:46,993
第二天一大早，我就接到电话
Next morning, bright and early,
I get the call.

1945
01:50:47,179 --> 01:50:49,549
我得去买点东西，你要不要去？
I've got to do some shopping. Want to go?

1946
01:50:49,749 --> 01:50:51,884
连接尼奇的电话都不是件易事
SAM: Getting a call from Nicky
wasn't easy anymore.

1947
01:50:52,084 --> 01:50:55,087
暗号都没有用了
我们得想新方法
Even the codes didn't work.
So we figured out another act.

1948
01:50:55,287 --> 01:50:59,725
若是电话被窃听
他们只能听关于犯罪的谈话
If a phone's tapped, the Feds can only
listen in on the stuff involving crimes.

1949
01:50:59,925 --> 01:51:03,162
例行通话时
他们必须在几分钟后挂断
On routine calls, they have
to click off after a few minutes.

1950
01:51:03,362 --> 01:51:06,101
我手肘好像扭到了
GINGER: I got a sprained fucking elbow.

1951
01:51:06,599 --> 01:51:07,934
三点见
Meet me at 3:00.

1952
01:51:08,134 --> 01:51:11,271
-在凯撒宫吗？
-这条路下去再一百码处
-At Caesar's?
-100 yards further down the road.

1953
01:51:11,370 --> 01:51:14,271
-为什么？
-别问了，到那儿就是了
-Why?
-Don't ask questions. Just be there.

1954
01:51:15,808 --> 01:51:19,321
苏西克理姆有件一模一样的衣服
Suzy Cream Cheese has the same outfit.

1955
01:51:20,279 --> 01:51:21,614
我看到个东西
GINGER: I saw something.

1956
01:51:21,814 --> 01:51:24,869
这东西好可爱
Something very cute.

1957
01:51:24,917 --> 01:51:28,754
他出门了，棕组
AGENT: Okay, he's out. It's the ant.
Brown unit.

1958
01:51:28,954 --> 01:51:31,691
他带着个替身，应该是法兰克
He's with the bogey. I think it's Frankie.

1959
01:51:31,891 --> 01:51:34,548
尼奇比我早出门…
SAM: Nicky started out before me...

1960
01:51:34,677 --> 01:51:37,512
因为他要出门越来越难了
because it wasn't that easy for him
to get around anymore.

1961
01:51:38,330 --> 01:51:40,967
尼奇到那儿都最起码得…
Nicky couldn't even go
for a ride without changing cars...

1962
01:51:41,167 --> 01:51:44,203
换六次车才甩得掉跟踪他的人
at least six times
before he could shake all his tails.

1963
01:51:44,403 --> 01:51:47,873
因为有飞机
所以他得用地下停车场
Because of the planes,
he had to use underground garages.

1964
01:51:48,073 --> 01:51:50,303
[Upbeat rock music]

1965
01:52:19,004 --> 01:52:21,641
在沙漠中央会面总让我紧张
SAM: Meeting in the desert
always made me nervous.

1966
01:52:21,841 --> 01:52:23,890
那是个可怕的地方
It's a scary place.

1967
01:52:24,376 --> 01:52:26,512
我当然也知道沙漠里的洞
I knew about the holes
in the desert, of course.

1968
01:52:26,712 --> 01:52:30,307
我张望的每一处都可能是个洞
And everywhere I looked,
there could have been a hole.

1969
01:52:32,017 --> 01:52:34,320
通常我与尼奇会面
能活着回来…
Normally, my prospects
of coming back alive...

1970
01:52:34,520 --> 01:52:37,525
机率是百分之九十九
from a meeting with Nicky
were 99 out of 100.

1971
01:52:38,891 --> 01:52:43,371
但这次，当我听他说
离道路几百码外…
But this time, when I heard him say a
couple of hundred yards down the road...

1972
01:52:43,729 --> 01:52:46,169
我想应该还有一半的机率吧
I gave myself 50-50.

1973
01:52:47,700 --> 01:52:49,895
[Sentimental instrumental music]

1974
01:53:06,852 --> 01:53:10,823
你他妈的跟别人
在背后捅我是什么意思？
Where the fuck you get off
talking to people behind my back?

1975
01:53:11,023 --> 01:53:13,693
-跟什么人？
-你以为我不会发现吗？
-What people?
-Did you think I wouldn't find out?

1976
01:53:13,893 --> 01:53:15,928
我根本不知道你在说什么
I don't even know what you're talking about.

1977
01:53:16,128 --> 01:53:21,033
你说我害你被盯？
我得因为你被人家念？
You said I'm bringing heat on you?
I gotta listen to people because of you?

1978
01:53:21,233 --> 01:53:24,236
你想搞走我？
你最好准备好自己的军队？
You're ordering me out? You better get
your own fucking army!

